#T_SP=webanno.custom.AspectRating|Aspect|ROLE_webanno.custom.AspectRating:OwnAspect_webanno.custom.AspectRatingOwnAspectLink|webanno.custom.AspectRating
#T_RL=de.tudarmstadt.ukp.dkpro.core.api.syntax.type.dependency.Dependency|DependencyType|flavor|BT_de.tudarmstadt.ukp.dkpro.core.api.lexmorph.type.pos.POS
#T_RL=webanno.custom.Valence|ValenceRating|BT_webanno.custom.AspectRating

#Text=Overall was very happy with my stay. Overall I considered it good value for money. Great location. It was very quiet and the staff were helpful. A wider choice of breakfast would have been good. A more extensive restaurant would be good also.

#Text=Wonderful. It was conveniently located near the Tawaramachi Station which in turn had elevators. Their staff are so polite. Cleaning is done on time everyday. I liked the daily breakfast as well. You also feel so secured since a key card is needed to go upstairs.

#Text=Value for money! Great location. The location and the facilities of the hotel are superb! Our check-in staff is a little bit rude which is rare in Japan. However, the other staffs were really nice and helpful. Room is rather small but in average size for Japan.
#Text=Excellent. Public bath is great. The environment is clean. The operation of central HVAC system (guess) is bit noisy.
#Text=Second APA experience. SPA and nice view from 14th floor. Tiny room (but standard in Japan)

#Text=Very Good. Great location, a little bit outside of the busier areas but still lots to see within walking distance. The coffee shop attached to the hotel was handy and was an easy way to get a quick breakfast.
#Text=Good. Opposite the subway station. Nice quiet neighbourhood. Location is not on JR line

#Text=Four-star stay for half the money. Good hospitality, lots of facilities in the hotel such as a spa, public bath, hairdresser, and an open market right outside the hotel. Good value for the money, and close to tourist attractions in Asakusa. The rooms were much smaller than I expected. Almost the size of a closet.
#Text=Good. breakfast just ok. Not much choice. Bed is OK. Bath is a bit small. Shower area not enough.

#Text=Exceptional. Staff is very nice and polite. Housekeeper is also very nice. There is a coin laundry provided. You can also get ice for free which I really like about this because I get it every night lol. I did not try breakfast so I can't tell. It is located at the tawaramachi station, ginza line which will lead you directly to shibuya! And it's also near to Ueno by only 2 stations to change to other many lines! It was so awesome! There are various kinds of restaurant around the area if you walk towards sensoji temple. Also, sensoji temple is only around 10 minutes by walking. Dust in the room. It gets dirty easily.

#Text=the manager and some staff treated me as a second rate visitor, the restaurant does not offer choice. the room was fantastic. the staff especially the manager was rude and arrogant, they seemed to not wanting other countries visiting
#Text=Very Good. Location is very convenient, hot spring facility is good

#Text=Perfect with small room and fantastic onsen. The room was okay but a bit small which is acceptable when compare a price to other hotels. Check-in and Check-out were easy and there aren't complicated. Location was fantastic, just a few steps from the metro station. there is an elevator both side of the station, you need to walk a bit to find an elevator. The best of this hotel is onsen which is located on the top floor, it was absolutely fantastic. You can see Tokyo Sky Tree from the outdoor bath. Amazing!! For the room, I would like to recommend a twins room if you have some spare budget. Totally 9.0/10 I would say, minus 1 point because of room size. Breakfast should be more variety and choice because there are just 3 choices of breakfast menu (All of them were about a bread, salad, selected beverage and eggs). The breakfast was served at the cafe restaurant on the ground floor.

#Text=Hotel was nice & Good location. Hotel was nice and clean overall but the space is really tight if you have big luggage. Only heating mode worked for air conditioning and night there was extremely hot
#Text=Good. SPA. Nil. Everything is ok.
#Text=Wonderful. Location, facilities, cleanliness. Rooms are a little small and toilet seats didn't have warmers.

#Text=A reasonably priced hotel in a popular area of Tokyo. Great for a short stay! A reasonably priced hotel in a busy area of Tokyo. The staff were friendly, approachable, and the rooms were clean and well maintained. There is a Komeda Coffee Shop downstairs, which provide good breakfasts. The rooms are very small, so I wouldn't recommend staying for a protracted length of time. The pillow is not great at all, which seems to be a standard across APA hotels, so I did not enjoy the most restful sleep.

#Text=A reasonably priced hotel in a popular area of Tokyo. Great for a short stay! A reasonably priced hotel in a busy area of Tokyo. The staff were friendly, approachable, and the rooms were clean and well maintained. There is a Komeda Coffee Shop downstairs, which provide good breakfasts. The rooms are very small, so I wouldn't recommend staying for a protracted length of time. The pillow is not great at all, which seems to be a standard across APA hotels, so I did not enjoy the most restful sleep.
#Text=Wonderful. It?fs so impressive how much luxury can be cramped on 11m2. Everything you need. Had my best sleep in Japan. Plus: Onsen till 1AM!
#Text=Wonderful. The location, accessibility and facilities. Price was great. Rooms were nice and clean but a bit dusty

#Text=Good. We like the hotspring. Quite suffocating in the room because of the warm air. And it was quite inconvenient that the air conditions couldn't change to cold air. It's fixed at warm air. We had to open the door instead which was really funny!!

#Text=Very comfortable beds and convenient to transportation, stores, etc. Fast check/in. Friendly and efficient customer service. My son and I were traveling together. I accidentally threw away his breakfast coupon, but the staff replaced it. Very comfortable beds, bath products (toothbrush, comb, etc), nice robe and the heating system was perfect. I get hot flushes, but the temperature in the room was perfect!
#Text=Wonderful. Very good location. Staff were nice and prompt with their service. Nothing much. Maybe the pillows? They were foam and flat.
#Text=Exceptional. I liked the hot bath on the 14th floor!

#Text=Nice and relaxing. Very close to a 7-11 and a metro station which made things convenient. Our room service staff was excellent. Room was decently sized for a Japanese hotel (could almost be considered spacious all things considered). Had easy to use laundry machine which made it nice for light packing. Not fond of needing to use a room key to power on the room. Accidentally forgot to take it with me once and had to wait for my friend to get back. This seems to be common among Japanese hotels though as every hotel I stayed at during the trip required the room key to turn on.

#Text=Convenient location to Metro. Close proximity to Asakusa line, which was great for visiting other areas of Tokyo. Good restaurants and sites a short walk away. The staff at check-in was very nice, the bed was comfortable, and it was very reasonably priced. The floor looked like it desperately needed to be cleaned. The cover on the bed looked a little dirty as well. Very cramped room, but we weren?ft in it enough for it to be an issue.
#Text=Good. good location, very clean. poor breakfast, only 3 options everyday, tv with only one english channel, small rooms

#Text=Great location and Value for money. Location is excellent, walking distance to Tawaramachi station. Staff were very helpful whenever you need their guidance. Small cafeteria downstairs, good enough for breakfast. Forex service available. Rooms were very clean with good amenities. Cant complain, but the rooms were small, didnt like the very flat pillows provided.
#Text=Very Good. The location. Room a bit small

#Text=Very Good. They had a nice public bath, which was for free. The location was?ft the best but it was a quiet area compared to those main Tokyo districts. The staffs were always nice and helpful. The bed mattress was too soft for me.
#Text=Very Good. excellent public bath, per recommended

#Text=Excellent choice. Great location! Staff was great, very helpful. Hotel was in general very very clean. I would choose this hotel again if i visited Tokyo another time. Our room was rather tiny. People with tattoo were unfortunately not allowed in the public bath. No smoking room. In order to smoke, you had to go out of the hotel and cross the street and go in a mart nearby, but it is not really too much of a fuss.

#Text=Excellent. Location is superb if you are planning to visit any landmarks in Asakusa (senso-ji temple, Tokyo Skytree, etc.). If you're after good ramen joint, Ichiran Ramen is less than a km away. The Tokyo Metro Station (Tawaramachi) and a few convenience stores are conveniently located a few 100 meters from the hotel. soundproofing of the room can be improved. we heard some weird noise (like a train coming and going) during the night.
#Text=Good. location. breakfast
#Text=Good. The amenities and staff were very nice and helpful. The room we were placed in was at a weird angle and thus quite small so it was difficult to move around with 3 checked bags.
#Text=Good. The staff were wonderful. The hotel is a little far away
#Text=Excellent. Small rooms
#Text=Good. Location, free toilets articles, room very clean. The room is too tiny

#Text=Convenitnely located hotel with a public bath! Highly recommended. I really enjoyed the public bath. The big TV in the room was also nice. The shower was easy to use. The staff were really friendly, helpful and could speak English. The room was very small. Nearly not enough space to fit luggage and move around.
#Text=Exceptional. Onsen on the rooftop. The hotel is just next to the metro. The room size..however it is an usual size of Tokyo's hotel I suppose.
#Text=Exceptional. The location, easy check in and out, luggage storage. In my room I heard a lot of noise and the elevator takes more time that it should
#Text=Wonderful. It was a great hotel, a little packed during check-out and check-in hours but that?fs to be expected. Rooms are a little smaller than other hotels I?fve stayed at in Japan.
#Text=Great value on the edge of Asakusa. Good deal on the edge of Asakusa. Good facilities, small room. You climb into the bed.

#Text=Clean, modern, well-situated (but with tiny rooms). The hotel is clean and modern. It's situated directly above the subway station in a very nice neighborhood. The staff is friendly. The included sento is a great value. Room is small as others have noted. Desk is too close to the bed.
#Text=Very Good. Close to the train station Lots of amenities Comfortable
#Text=Excellent. Spa, cleanness. Room size for 2, temperature

#Text=Idle location for Akihabara, Senso-Ji and 2 mins from Ginza gets you anywhere cheaply! Perfect. The rooms are small (as you would expect) but pretty ideal, comes with everything you need, bed is comfy and wifi is excellent. You don't go to Tokyo to spend time in your room, you can happily relax all day if you wanted to. The bakery run by the old lady next door is great for breakfast / dinner! Main window didn't open (as it was a major fire escape and only opened to escape) which meant it was a bit hot and stuffy. Once had figured out the air humidifier it was better, but could have done with English explanation rather than googling for manuals.
#Text=Good. Location
#Text=Good. Double Room a little tiny
#Text=Good. I like the property and our room. The breakfast

#Text=Good. The hotel has a good position, it offers many services and is located in beautiful area. The staff is nice, speak at a sufficient level in English and helped us when we needed. The double room where we slept was too small. Really it was not possible to keep our luggages opened and going to the toilet at the same time. The window could not be opened. I cannot suggest to stay in this hotel for more than one or two nights honestly.

#Text=Its okay for this kind of price. Breakfast is good. 14/F bath was excellent. Metro station just around the corner. Room small. Lift slow. Too many people at the reception. Check in time is not good. Should allow early as 2:00PM.

#Text=Excellent. Value for money, stone throw to Tawaramachi MRT station, 15walk to Asakusa Shrine. Perfect for the price u pay. The front desk didn?ft allow me to check in earlier as I arrived hotel at 12:30pm due to morning flight, despite there are rooms available. The staff asking for extra 1000 Yen per room for early check in which I think is not about the money, is the service. I?fve try request during booking but this little thing tarnished the credit.
#Text=Good. Good position . Fast check in and out. People is nice. The room is very clean . The room is small and the bed is too soft. The breakfast is simple.

#Text=Good. Nice hotel in a very convenient location, close to the sights of Asakusa. Complimentary spa a great bonus after a day of sightseeing. Rooms on the small side. Breakfast not included, but a limited version available at the next door restaurant.
#Text=Good. The best thing was the Span, the rest was good but nothing special. The space of the rooms are small, and there is not wardrobe.

#Text=Clean hotel that offers privacy, but you can stay for much cheaper in Tokyo. Easy to access from the Metro and a great location in Taito-ku. Big comfy bed, big TV, nice private bathroom. Easy check in/out, and a Komeda coffee shop connected to the lobby. A bit pricey compared to other economy options in Tokyo. The public bath on the top floor did not allow people with tattoos to enter, an antiquated restriction that didn't make sense in a hotel filled with foreign travelers.

#Text=Clean rooms, comfy pillows, chic environment. They had a hot bath area, separate for women and men. Tokyo sized room with queen bed but with all amenities and value for money. Hotel/room looks very chic and modern. Good security and nice location, close to the Metro station.
#Text=Overall it was very good. Staffs and the location is really good. Breakfast

#Text=Perfect Hotel Location for Explore Asakusa. Location was perfect, only 1 minute walk from Tarawamachi Station easy way to Shibuya, Shinjuku, Ueno and Ginza. 9 minute walk to Sensoji and perfect place if you want have a time around Asakusa, sky tree tower and nakamise market. Check in with modern style, staff was friendly even they speak little english. The room are too small but I'm fully understand it Japanese standard.
#Text=Very Good. Everything else. The room is too small
#Text=Excellent. Cleaning staff very friendly and accommodating. Check-in was efficient but very impersonal
#Text=Exceptional. Pillow are too thin

#Text=Good value for money. Room was a comfortable size for two guests Very discreet and effective cleaning staff Comfortable bed. Not close to JR station Slow elevators Unable to use onsen as a couple and due to having tattoos Only one coin washing machine and drier in 14F bathroom making it difficult to accessibly wash clothes

#Text=Location was key to us enjoying this stay. But good hotel. Breakfast was nice. Not massive though. Location was spot on. Staff very helpful. Room size was tiny. Money spent on the room and breakfast didn't feel right. Of 5 hotels we stayed in this was the bottom one.
#Text=Great location. Convenient. Comfortable rooms. Comfortable rooms with ensuite. Tiny size but this is Tokyo. There is an Onsen on the top floor with men and women separated.
#Text=Good. Near Tawaramachi station. Too much noise at the hall of the second floor.
#Text=Very Good. Good value for money, you get what you pay for. Metro is right at the corner. Ueno station is 1km away. Poor breakfast in cafe
#Text=Very good. I liked Cleanliness and Locality. Very compact. No wardrobe. No space to keep baggage.

#Text=Bath on the rooftop. Facilities and bath on the rooftop... Shiseido products in the rooms and drinkable/filtered water in bathroom... Little kimonos and slipers we got for rooms ?? Size of the room... it's really tiny... Didn't have space to open my suitcase and no wardrobe to store your clothes ??

#Text=Good location, easy access. It's located in the nice Asakusa neighbourhood, easily connected by public transport. The room is small, as expected for a room in Tokyo. Our room was on the 13th floor with a view of the Sky Tree. The shower water was very powerful, which I find very important after a long day of sightseeing. The two of us stayed there for four nights, but they only gave 1 bottle of water on two of the four days.

#Text=Great location and good room. Breakfast can be improved. Loved the location, clean, and good room. Great facility, especially for the price. Room could have been cleaner. Breakfast was not a buffet, they had a collaboration with a cafe attached to the hotel, which served breakfast too. You can only choose from 3 courses for breakfast, and the amount was little.
#Text=It was great. Clean room. Old tv
#Text=Very clean hotel, new and nice bathroom. The room is very clean. The onzen is nice. I love the ice machine on the 14th FL. The room is quite small.
#Text=Concierge service will be nice traveling alone sometimes hard to get around. Location?A????Awarmness of dtuff. Room was little tight. For the rate I paid I'd like to be higher floor.

#Text=Superb location, cozy room but would come again. Lovely entrance, staff helpful and many complementary items were provided. Room was smaller than expected. Could fit suitcase just in, with a narrow hallway and bedroom. It was cozy to say the least. But location superb! Still a good 20mins from JR station if you decide not to take the subway.
#Text=Very Good. Loved the fact that each APA hotel seems to have a free spa included (i.e., japanese-style communal hot tub)
#Text=Good. Bed linen is good. Pillows

#Text=Very cramped rooms but good location. Reception area was nice and there was a good spa. Location was good, very close to a metro station. The rooms were very cramped and the pillows very flat. The breakfast at the coffee shop was very poor. We went to a local bakery instead.
#Text=Very Good. Good location. Windows - not posible to see trough or open

#Text=Good. Staff very nice and everything was as expected. Pillows and bed are hard making it not so nice for sleeping. Also in my room the AC was not following the inputs and kept heating the room to 23C making it not nice to sleep (Happened both times I was there)
#Text=Exceptional. good size rooms and beds. had everything you needed. Great location very close to an important metro line

#Text=I will stay again despite room size. But, even though the room is small, I still plan on staying there because it is very nice and clean and perfect for visiting all the districts. Ginza line is right next door! Also the staff was amazingly helpful, nice and caring! Room was really cramped. No room to move around specially if your visiting to shop. But if just for business, you'll be fine.

#Text=Price/Value Unbeatable, Great Spa (Onsen). The onsens are open late and just wonderful. The women's outdoor onsen has a view of the Skytree Tower and both the men's and women's onsens include a jacuzzi. The price and location are unbeatable. The room was incredibly small but we expected that and made it work. The room could have used two luggage stands but we made do with using the chair for one and sticking the bags at the foot of the bed. It would have been nice to be able to open the window too.
#Text=Exceptional. good location, easy to check in-out. The space of room is quite small.
#Text=Great neighbourhood excellent access. The osen bath was wonderful. An extra pillow
#Text=Excellent. Great location, good facilities, nice bath. Too crowded in the morning Impersonal

#Text=Very nice hotel in good location. Very clean Good location, 2 minutes walk to subway station Fast internet All necessary facilities provided Cleaning ladies were leaving clean towels and new set of cosmetics in front of the door even when ?do not disturb?h hangs on the door. Rooms are very small, it is hard to move inside when you open your luggage Bathroom is tiny
#Text=Good. You cannot open the window even a little bit to get a fresh air The hallways are very cold
#Text=I would definitely come back for next stay. Spa was super relaxing and refreshing and good quality of amenities to add to it.
#Text=Nice place to sleep, but not much more. Nice Spa (actually only a hot bath). Room was pretty small. Hard to even put the suitcase somewhere.

#Text=Good. I was quite shocked to find that APA distributes fascist propaganda masquerading as "theoretical history" into each room. Some highlights: Nanking massacre never happened, like comfort women this is a western conspiracy; Japan needs to re-militarize and build offensive power, etc. Highly offending and I'm slightly nauseous to have spent my money there.
#Text=Exceptional. Great hot spa. Breakfast was ok, but a bit expensive for the small meal
#Text=Excellent. The mattress was in poor condition and the pillow was too thin.

#Text=Very Good. This is a very nice place right in front of the station making transportation very convenient. Few minutes walk to Sensoji Temple, and Ueno station. The onsen is a great place to relax after the long day. However the room is a bit too small even for two people. We barely had enough space to unpack our luggages.
#Text=Excellent. Good location, near subway. No drinking water in room
#Text=Wonderful. The hotel was clean and friendly. Our room was extremely small

#Text=I had a pleasant stay and really enjoyed the comfortable bed.. Very convenient for metro. Room very clean and quiet. Bed very comfortable. A thick duvet was supplied. I did not need it and it occupied a lot of space.
#Text=Very Good. . .
#Text=Good value. - Great location. - Great onsen. - Comfortable bed. - AC not working for the first night. - Charged 10$ for a lost door card. - Poor sound proofing.

#Text=Wonderful. Location is right next to train station, close to the temple attraction area. Clean, great indoor and outdoor onsen. Staff is helpful. Check in is a hybrid self check-in system which involves a front desk associate. I don?ft find it any more efficient than normal to have the guest click a few buttons on a big screen and pick up the key issues by the machine. Instead, it took away the excellent hospitality and personal touch that Japan usually offers.
#Text=Good. The location is near to elevator to Tawaramachi station. So, during raining time, at least you can quickly get to the station via the elevator. Nothing
#Text=Excellent. Bed was comfortable. Pillows were small and flat. When I asked for an extra pillow they told me they had no extras. TV only had about 10 free channels, all but one in Japanese.

#Text=Exactly what we needed - will stay again for sure. Althou rooms were a little small we expected that - was really close to Senso-Ji Temple and other great Asakusa awsomeness - will def stay again - breakfast was simple but delish and perfectly sized - thanks! As I said the rooms are a bit small but we expected that - very clean and the staff were fantastic

#Text=I really enjoyed my stay here. It met all my expectations. The location is fantastic! The front desk is okay, I particularly liked the electronic check-in process. I enjoyed the grand spa as well. Breakfast didn't seem like value for money to me, so I opted for other options.
#Text=Good. Near subway station! Excellent

#Text=Convenient hotel for short term stays. - Staff friendly and helpful - Nice Onsen - Convenient location to explore Asakusa and Ueno area. - Waiting times for elevators too long - Rooms are rather small (I'd stay again for a short 2-3 day visit, but not longer)

#Text=All in all, we loved our stay here. The staff made a huge difference! They were very helpful! Everything! The staff was exceptional! They helped us when we left our money in our room despite us checking out that day. The cleaner was also very friendly :). The size of the room. The pillow?

#Text=Pleasant stay. Not too great for all round traveling. The room and its amenities was comfortable since I was traveling alone and was out all day long. Couldn?ft imagine staying with two people though. I had no problem with the size of the bed (177cm), it slept fine. Clean towels and bathroom supplies everyday. No disturbance of other guests. In the evening it wasn?ft a madhouse. Which isn?ft a bad thing if you?fre not interested in nightlife. It?fs nice to stroll around the area and visit Senso-Ji. Restaurants generally serve their last meal around 22:00. They?fd let me store my luggage before and after check in so I could roam around. The hotel offers things such as laundry, vending machines and a public bath (NO tattoos). There?fs a coffee house attached to the hotel which closes at 23:00. The travel distance to popular attractions was doable. I wouldn?ft recommend it if you?fd like to repeatedly visit the west side of Tokyo (Shinjuku, Shibuya etc). I planned the trip so that I could explore Ueno/Tokyo central/Ginza. JR line is a 15 min walk. Metro is across the street. I didn?ft like the check in since the lady behind the desk felt rather rushed and agitated. She gave no explanation about my room or the amenities in and around the hotel.

#Text=Nice location with fantastic suroundings. The location was nice and practical. The overall hotel was good. The hotel so near to the metro station. The most critical and strange was that the staff not speaking English. It is very essential that the front desk staff should speak English. I believe this should be a must condition for booking.com.

#Text=A nice hotel close to subway. Not much facilities inside. Very clean room, good location very close to subway (around 50 m). The onsen is fine. Overall, the hotel is very nice and modern. The room is definitely too small: it is almost impossible to tidy the suitcase except using the (small) desk. Breakfast is possible in a nearby restaurant, but there is a limited choice and it is rather expensive. There are almost no facilities in the hotel, for instance only one beverage dispenser, with limit choice of beverages. All together, it is not fully confortable. When I was there, the WIFI connection was very slow.
#Text=Wonderful. Helpful staff, clean room, well equipped
#Text=Exceptional. Train station Tawarimachi is very close by, 711 is across the street, walking distance to Asakusa Kaminarimon Gate. Small, no closet space but expected but still manageable
#Text=A great room for a great price. The staff were a great help! We had a small issue with our bathroom door and we were given all care and attention to make us happy! Nothing bad to say!

#Text=Great hotel. The localization is really good! All the infrastructure is awesome and we had a really good time in the hotel! The staff were also very nice and the payment was really simple using an international credit card.
#Text=Good. Reception are friendly & helpful. Check in need to wait till 3pm
#Text=Great! Very near subway statio. A little too expensive

#Text=We had a great stay ! Thank you. The front desk staff were very friendly and helpful. The hotel was easy to locate and only 2 minute walk to the metro station. The location is convenient and near Yoshinoya, 7-11, and greek eatery. The pajama set in the room available to us was great! Our room was too small. There was very little space for our luggage. Pillows were flat and not what I expected.

#Text=Pleasant hotel to stay in. The environment (14th floor) was private and quiet. Wifi is too weak. Most of the time it is not working well. I was staying at Level 14 (the highest floor). The bed is also too soft for me though it is still on the confortable side. Room is even smaller than those usual small double bed room in hotels in Japan.
#Text=Good. Service. The room size

#Text=New hotel. Good location. Great hot bath. Small room. Very good location near Asakusa and very close to Ginza line. New hotel. The room was small. The staff helpful. Best thing about the hotel is the modern onsen (hot bath) in the 14th floor. Two big pools, one inside, one outside. That made the difference for me. Room very small. No wardrobe. I changed my room because in the first one you couldn?ft open the window. Room change no problem. There is no bar. Entrance area always crowded, most guests are tourists. Breakfast at cafe next door.

#Text=Exceptional. The staff was lovely, very friendly and polite! And the public bath on the 14th floor was super nice! Very hygenic and clean hotel. The toilet in the room was quite close to the wall, so it felt a bit cramped.
#Text=its a nice, quite neighborhood and good location hotel. location
#Text=Brilliant! Excellent location, very close to stations. Clean, friendly staff. Room is standard Tokyo size - a little small. Pillows uncomfortable!

#Text=great. Onsen and Hot Bath. We would appreciate a small bed for our Daugther even if she was 5 years old. I did not realise when I booked the room there was only one Bed for 3 people, it should have been an added option.
#Text=Exceptional. location is good, room is small but extremely clean & tidy with a large 55" TV. It is a good deal for just around 100USD per night. Nil
